ACT:
 Income Tax Act, 1922---Section 25-A(3)--Claims for partition and disruption of the Hindu Undivided Family disallowed by I.T.O.--Appeal under the Act filed against the orders of I.T.O. also dismissed--No reference under the Act challenging the Tribunal's order dismissing the appeal was taken, but subsequently got a prelminary decree for parti- tion, passed by the civil court during the pendency of the appeal--Whether the Income Tax Authorities are bound by the subsequent partition decree of the civil court.
 Right of management--Hindu Law--Joint Hindu Undivided Family-Whether a junior member of the family can act as a karta with the consent of all the other members, if the senior member gives up his right.
 
